{
  "stem": "13874.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "From father's side was Leopold and Teresa.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Her first-- her maiden name was [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "From my mother's side, it was Meyer and Nanni Laub.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We-- actually, our family goes back up to 1800 and before.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I have traced it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, my father's side, they all came from the same area.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was born in Hornberg.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I think there are only Sellings there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He came-- he came-- in Germany, he came from Hornberg.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] My father's great grandfather, whose name was Isaac, lived-- I think was the first one who adopted the name Selling, because it was after 19-- after 1816, when the Jews in Bavaria could adopt name.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "How he got his name, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It's so English-sounding, nobody will believe me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "On my mother's side, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] her mother's maiden name was Kramer, and they got the name 1816, same time, when Jews taken from Northern Bavaria, when those-- when the Jews were allowed to take family names.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So local Catholic priest asked my ancestor to perpetuate his name by adopting it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And to reconcile with some other branches of the family.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Regular public school, of course and than after the fourth grade, we went to middle school, [NON-ENGLISH], and I was 16.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was in 1934, when the Nazis were in power, and I had to leave.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I wanted to study further, but I couldn't.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I had only ten.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Personally, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] very moderate and not very religious, and now I would call myself an atheist, more or less.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But family history was fairly orthodox.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Orthodox was the only Jewish religion in Germany at that time, especially in the small towns.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was also a reform congregation in Berlin and Frankfurt.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
